description: A herbaceous perennial, dicotyledonous plant with oblanceolate shaped leaves that show lobate margins and pinnate venation. It's flower is made up of yellow or orange ray florets.
A herbaceous perennial, dicotyledonous plant that has compound basal leaves divided into three broad leaflets which are lobed. Flowers are golden yellow and glossy with 5 petals.

description: A semi-evergreen, dicotyledonous shrub that can grow up to 3.7 meters tall. It has lance-shaped leaves that are finely toothed, which are green on top and whitish with downy hairs underneath. The plant produces small, trumpet-shaped flowers that are usually purple, sometimes white.

A herbaceous, dicotyledonous plant with simple, opposite leaves that are lanceolate and have toothed margins. The plant is typically monoecious with male and female flowers appearing on a single plant

A dicotyledonous, vigorous, deciduous climber with palmately compound leaves that consist of five ovate coarsely serrate leaflets. The leaf venation is palmate. The plant produces inconspicuous green flowers and blue-black berries.

description: A herbaceous, dicotyledonous plant with compound leaves that are divided into three sub-leaflets. The leaflets have toothed margins and pinnate venation. The plant produces an umble of white flowers in early summer.

A herbaceous, dicotyledonous plant that can grow up to 3 meters tall1. It has simple, sagittate (arrowhead-shaped) leaves that are dull green above and paler below, with entire margins. The plant produces trumpet-shaped flowers that are usually white, sometimes with pink windows, and the flowers are radially symmetrical with five fused petals.

A perennial grass with long, creeping rhizomes. Its leaves are linear with a prominent midrib, and the margins are often scabrous. The flowers are arranged in spikelets, each containing several florets, and the inflorescence is a panicle.

description: A submerged aquatic plant with finely divided, whorled leaves. The leaves are linear or lanceolate and have serrated margins. The plant lacks true roots and instead has modified stems for anchorage. Its flowers are inconspicuous and are borne singly or in clusters in the leaf axils.

An evergreen, herbaceous, dicotyledonous plant. It has spoon-shaped leaves that grow in a rosette, with toothed leaf margins. The leaf venation is not distinct but resembles pinnate. The plant produces small, solitary, yellow-centered white daisies from early spring to late summer. Each flower head is a composite of many sessile flowers with white ray florets and yellow disc florets.

An annual or biennial herb with deeply lobed, heart-shaped basal leaves and smaller, lanceolate stem leaves with toothed margins. The veins on the leaves are pinnate. The plant produces small, white flowers in racemes, and each flower has four petals arranged in a cross shape.

A perennial herb with broad, oval-shaped leaves that have parallel venation and entire margins. The plant produces inconspicuous flowers arranged in spikes, with each flower having four small petals. The inflorescence is a dense spike at the top of a long, slender stem.

An annual herb with opposite, ovate leaves that have entire margins and prominent parallel veins. The plant produces small, white flowers with five deeply lobed petals. The flowers are borne singly on slender stalks arising from the leaf axils.

A perennial fern with simple, strap-shaped leaves that lack distinct leaflets. The margins of the leaves are entire, and the venation is parallel. The plant produces inconspicuous greenish or yellowish flowers arranged in clusters called sori on the undersides of the leaves.

A perennial tuberous plant with heart-shaped leaves that have deeply lobed margins. The venation is palmate. The plant produces delicate, nodding flowers with reflexed petals in shades of pink, white, or purple. The flowers are borne singly on slender stems arising from the center of the rosette of leaves.

A perennial herb with linear, grass-like leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces spikes of small, bell-shaped flowers in shades of lavender or white. The inflorescence is a raceme or panicle arising from the base of the leaves.

A perennial herbaceous plant with leathery, palmately lobed leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces nodding flowers with five petal-like sepals in shades of pink, purple, or white. The flowers are borne singly or in clusters on stout stems emerging from the center of the rosette of leaves.

A perennial herbaceous plant with linear, strap-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces small, bell-shaped flowers that are usually pale pink or white. The flowers are borne on short stalks in clusters at the base of the leaves.

A trailing evergreen perennial with ovate leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are glossy green with creamy-white margins. The plant produces large, funnel-shaped flowers in shades of blue or purple. The flowers are solitary and arise from the leaf axils.

description: A fast-growing evergreen conifer with scale-like leaves arranged in flattened sprays. The leaves have entire margins, and the plant produces small, spherical cones. The cones are borne upright on the branches and mature to brown.

description: A deciduous tree with trifoliate leaves that have serrated margins. The venation is palmate. The plant produces inconspicuous flowers arranged in small clusters, followed by winged fruits called samaras. The bark is notable for its peeling, coppery-brown appearance.

A deciduous tree with palmately compound leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces showy, upright panicles of white flowers with yellow or red markings. Each flower has four or five petals. The fruits are large, spiny capsules containing shiny brown seeds.

description: A succulent perennial with rosettes of rigid, sword-shaped leaves that have spiny margins. The plant produces a tall flowering stalk with numerous yellow or greenish flowers. The inflorescence is a panicle or raceme.

An evergreen conifer with stiff, sharply pointed leaves arranged in whorls around the branches. The leaves have entire margins. The plant produces separate male and female cones on the same tree. The female cones are large and round, while the male cones are smaller and cylindrical.

An evergreen shrub or small tree with elliptical leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces urn-shaped white or pink flowers that are borne in clusters. The flowers have five petals and are often tinged with red. The fruits resemble strawberries and are edible.

An evergreen shrub with holly-like leaves that have spiny margins. The plant produces bright orange-yellow flowers in clusters. Each flower has six petals and is fragrant. The flowers are followed by blue-black berries that are attractive to birds.

description: An evergreen shrub with small, ovate leaves that have entire margins. The venation is inconspicuous. The plant produces small, greenish-yellow flowers in the spring. The flowers are borne in clusters at the tips of the branches.

An evergreen shrub with glossy, trifoliate leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces clusters of fragrant, white flowers with four or five petals. The flowers are star-shaped and resemble orange blossoms, hence the common name.

description: A perennial herb with strap-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces clusters of tubular, orange or yellow flowers on stout stems. The flowers are trumpet-shaped and are arranged in umbels.

A vigorous vine with leathery, lanceolate leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces fragrant, star-shaped white flowers in clusters. The flowers have six to eight petals and are borne in axillary panicles.

A palm-like evergreen tree with long, sword-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are arranged in a dense rosette at the top of the trunk. The plant produces panicles of small, fragrant, white flowers followed by small, spherical berries.

A deciduous shrub with ovate leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces clusters of small, white flowers in the spring, followed by clusters of glossy black berries. The stems exhibit vibrant orange and red colors in winter, providing striking ornamental interest.

An evergreen shrub with lanceolate leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces clusters of highly fragrant, pale pink flowers in late winter to early spring. The flowers are tubular and are borne in dense clusters at the ends of the branches.

An evergreen shrub with large, palmately lobed leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces small, white flowers in spherical umbels in the fall. The flowers are followed by small, black berries that are attractive to birds.

An evergreen shrub with leathery, oval leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are glossy green above and pale green below. The plant produces inconspicuous flowers followed by small, purple berries. The flowers are borne in axillary clusters.

A deciduous shrub with ovate leaves that have wavy margins. The plant produces clusters of fragrant, spidery yellow flowers in late winter to early spring. The flowers are borne on bare branches and are followed by woody capsules that split open to release the seeds.

description: An evergreen tree or shrub with glossy, spiny leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces small, white flowers in the spring, followed by bright red berries that persist through the winter. The flowers are inconspicuous and are borne in axillary clusters.

A semi-evergreen shrub with oval leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces small, white flowers in panicles in late spring to early summer. The flowers are followed by small, black berries that are attractive to birds.

description: A tropical vine with large, heart-shaped leaves that have deep cuts or perforations. The leaves have entire margins. The plant produces a large, white spadix surrounded by a green spathe. The inflorescence is borne on a long, stout stem arising from the center of the leaf rosette.

A bulbous perennial with linear leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces dense spikes of small, bell-shaped flowers in shades of blue or purple. The flowers are tightly packed and resemble clusters of grapes, hence the common name.

description: A perennial herb with long, sword-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are arranged in a dense rosette and may be green, bronze, or variegated. The plant produces tall spikes of tubular flowers in shades of red, orange, or yellow.

A hybrid evergreen shrub with glossy, elliptical leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are bright red when young, maturing to dark green. The plant produces small, white flowers in corymbs in late spring to early summer. The flowers are followed by small red fruits.

A tall, clump-forming bamboo with lanceolate leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are bright green and may be tinged with yellow or red in bright sunlight. The plant produces small, greenish flowers in panicles at the ends of the culms.

A deciduous tree with ovate leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces small, white flowers in clusters in the spring, followed by small black fruits. The bark is particularly ornamental, with peeling layers that reveal coppery-brown inner bark.

A large deciduous tree with deeply lobed leaves that have entire or shallowly lobed margins. The plant produces inconspicuous flowers in catkins in the spring, followed by acorns. The bark is rough and deeply fissured.

description: An evergreen shrub with linear leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are aromatic and are commonly used as a culinary herb. The plant produces small, tubular flowers in shades of blue, purple, pink, or white. The flowers are borne in terminal spikes.

A succulent perennial with stiff, sword-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are mottled with yellow or cream-colored variegation. The plant produces clusters of small, tubular white flowers on tall stalks.

An evergreen shrub with glossy, ovate leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces small, fragrant white flowers in winter. The flowers are followed by glossy black berries. The plant is valued for its winter interest and fragrance.

A perennial succulent with rosettes of fleshy leaves that have cobweb-like hairs and entire margins. The plant produces clusters of small, star-shaped flowers in shades of pink, red, or white. The flowers are borne on tall stalks above the rosettes.

An evergreen shrub with glossy, ovate leaves that have entire margins. The plant produces fragrant, white or pink flowers in dense clusters in the spring. The flowers are followed by bright red berries that persist through the winter. The plant is valued for its ornamental foliage and berries.

A tropical perennial with lanceolate leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are glossy green and may be variegated. The plant produces white flowers with a spathe and spadix. The flowers are borne on tall stalks arising from the center of the plant.

An evergreen conifer with linear leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are dark green and arranged spirally around the branches. The plant produces inconspicuous flowers followed by red, fleshy arils enclosing the seeds. The seeds are highly poisonous.

A low-growing evergreen shrub with ovate leaves that have serrated margins. The plant produces small, tubular white flowers in rounded clusters in the spring. The flowers are followed by metallic blue-black berries. The plant is valued for its ornamental foliage and berries.

A tropical perennial with pinnate leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are glossy green and arise from thick, succulent stems. The plant produces small, spathe-like flowers that are inconspicuous. The flowers are rarely seen in cultivation.

An aquatic perennial with lance-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically cordate at the base and exhibit parallel venation. It produces spikes of lavender-blue flowers arranged in a dense, elongated cluster called a spike inflorescence.

A perennial herb with basal rosettes of elliptic leaves that have crenate margins. The leaves are typically pubescent and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces clusters of fragrant, five-petaled flowers in shades of yellow, white, or pink in early spring. The flowers are borne on short stalks rising from the center of the rosette.

A perennial herb with opposite, lanceolate leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are typically pubescent and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces dense spikes of tubular, purple flowers with two lips in summer. The flowers are densely packed on the spike and attract pollinators.

A perennial herb with deeply dissected, fern-like leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are covered with fine hairs and exhibit palmate venation. It produces solitary, bell-shaped flowers with six petals in shades of purple, white, or pink. The flowers emerge in early spring and are followed by feathery seed heads.

An annual herb with lanceolate leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are arranged oppositely along the stem and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces yellow, two-lipped flowers with a distinctive inflated calyx in summer. The flowers are borne in terminal spikes.

A perennial herb with lanceolate to ovate leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are usually pubescent and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces bright orange-yellow flowers with dark brown centers in late summer to early fall. The flowers are daisy-like and borne on stiff, hairy stems.

A perennial herb with ovate to lanceolate leaves that have entire to serrated margins. The leaves are typically gray-green and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces spikes of tubular flowers in shades of blue, purple, pink, or white in late spring to summer. The flowers are arranged in terminal inflorescences.

A woody vine with palmately lobed leaves that have a yellow-golden center and green margins. The leaves are typically glossy and exhibit palmate venation. It produces small, greenish-yellow flowers in late summer to early fall. The flowers are inconspicuous and arranged in umbels.

A herbaceous perennial with circular, palmately lobed leaves that have finely serrated margins. The leaves are usually velvety and exhibit palmate venation. It produces small, chartreuse-yellow flowers in dense clusters in late spring to early summer. The flowers have no petals and are borne on erect stems.

A deciduous to semi-evergreen shrub with ovate to elliptic leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically glossy and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces clusters of tubular, fragrant flowers in shades of pink, white, or lavender from late spring to fall. The flowers are borne in terminal or axillary cymes.

A herbaceous perennial with deeply lobed, ovate leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are typically glossy and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces tall spikes of tubular, white or purple flowers with purple bracts in summer. The flowers are borne in dense, terminal racemes.

description: A compact, evergreen perennial with linear leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically basal and exhibit parallel venation. It produces dense, rounded clusters of small, pink, white, or red flowers on stiff stems in late spring to early summer. The flowers are borne in umbels.

A deciduous shrub or small tree with rounded, serrated leaves. The leaves are typically alternate and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces small, yellow-green catkins in late winter to early spring before the leaves emerge. The flowers are borne in clusters and are wind-pollinated.

description: A drought-tolerant perennial with linear, gray-green leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are arranged spirally along the stem and exhibit parallel venation. It produces tall spikes of lime-green flowers surrounded by chartreuse bracts in late spring to early summer. The flowers are borne in terminal cymes.

A deciduous conifer with linear, flattened needles that have a fine, opposite arrangement. The needles exhibit parallel venation. It produces small, round cones in late summer to fall that mature to brown. The cones are borne on the branches and disintegrate to release seeds.

A perennial grass with arching, green leaves that have horizontal, golden-yellow bands. The leaves are typically linear and exhibit parallel venation. It produces feathery, pinkish plumes in late summer to fall that rise above the foliage. The inflorescence is terminal and resembles a bottlebrush.

A clump-forming perennial grass with narrow, arching leaves that have finely serrated margins. The leaves are typically green and exhibit parallel venation. It produces tall, feathery panicles of golden-brown flowers in summer. The inflorescence is open and airy, adding movement to the landscape.

description: A herbaceous perennial with lanceolate leaves that have entire to serrated margins. The leaves are typically alternate and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces clusters of daisy-like flowers with numerous violet-blue or pinkish rays surrounding yellow disk florets in late summer to fall. The flowers are borne in terminal corymbs.

A deciduous shrub or small tree with ovate to elliptic leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically alternate and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces large, fragrant, star-shaped flowers with numerous white or pink tepals in early spring. The flowers are solitary or borne in small clusters.

description: A herbaceous perennial with kidney-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically basal and exhibit palmate venation. It produces bright yellow, bowl-shaped flowers in early spring. The flowers are borne singly on erect stems rising above the foliage.

A deciduous shrub with ovate to lanceolate leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are typically arranged oppositely along the stem and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces bright yellow, bell-shaped flowers in early spring before the leaves emerge. The flowers are borne profusely along the stems.

A herbaceous perennial with rosettes of linear to spatulate leaves that have entire to slightly toothed margins. The leaves are typically basal and exhibit parallel venation. It produces showy, star-shaped flowers in shades of pink, red, orange, white, or yellow in late spring to early summer. The flowers are borne on slender stalks rising above the foliage.

description: A perennial aquatic plant with long, linear leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically basal and exhibit parallel venation. It produces cylindrical, brownish flower spikes in summer. The flower spikes are borne on erect stems and are densely packed with tiny, unisexual flowers.

A deciduous tree with palmately lobed leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are typically arranged opposite and exhibit palmate venation. It produces inconspicuous, red to purple flowers in spring. The flowers are borne in small clusters, followed by winged samaras.

A deciduous tree with triangular to diamond-shaped leaves that have doubly serrated margins. The leaves are typically arranged alternately and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces inconspicuous, yellow-brown catkins in spring before the leaves emerge. The catkins are pendulous and borne in clusters.

A rhizomatous perennial with linear, sword-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically basal and exhibit parallel venation. It produces large, yellow, iris-like flowers with six petals and yellow-orange markings in late spring to early summer. The flowers are borne on erect stems.

An annual or biennial herb with lanceolate leaves that have entire to slightly toothed margins. The leaves are typically alternate and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces solitary, blue, pink, or white flowers with a prominent central disk in summer. The flowers are borne singly on slender stems.

description: A deciduous shrub or small tree with ovate to elliptic leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically arranged alternately and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces large, plume-like inflorescences called panicles in late spring to summer. The inflorescences are covered in tiny, hair-like filaments that give them a smoky appearance.

A bulbous perennial with lanceolate leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically alternate and exhibit parallel venation. It produces nodding, bell-shaped flowers with checkered patterns in shades of purple, pink, or white in spring. The flowers are solitary or borne in umbels.

A deciduous tree with fan-shaped leaves that have parallel venation. The leaves are typically alternate and have entire margins. It produces inconspicuous, yellow-green flowers in spring. The flowers are dioecious, with male flowers borne in catkins and female flowers borne on short stalks.

A herbaceous perennial with lanceolate leaves that have serrated margins. The leaves are typically basal and exhibit parallel venation. It produces solitary, daisy-like flowers with white rays and yellow disk florets in late spring to summer. The flowers are borne on erect stems rising above the foliage.

A clump-forming perennial with upright, vase-shaped fronds that have deeply lobed, pinnate segments. The fronds are typically light green and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces spore-bearing structures called sori on the undersides of fertile fronds in summer. The sori are arranged in two rows on either side of the midrib.

A deciduous tree with ovate to elliptic leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically alternate and exhibit pinnate venation. It produces inconspicuous, yellow-green flowers in spring. The flowers are borne in catkins.

A rhizomatous perennial with large, paddle-shaped leaves that have entire margins. The leaves are typically arranged alternately and exhibit pinnate venation.
